Linear Regression

looking at the relationship between 2 quantitative variables. for instance, is Danielleâs grumpiness level related to the amount of sleep the baby gets?

regression considers a possible linear relationship.

\(H_0:\) thereâs no linear relationship between the variables. the slope of the line of best-fit is zero.

\(H_a:\) thereâs a linear relationship between the variables. the slope of the line of best-fit is non-zero.

visualization is essential when doing regression since have to check if relationship appears linear.

parenting <- read_excel("parenting.xlsx")
